\fs36 \cf2 About
\fs24 \cf0 \
This template is designed to produce an essay in the Chicago Style format. However, you should check the exact guidelines of the institution to which you are submitting your essay, because formatting expectations can vary (such as whether there should be a separate title page, whether footnotes should appear at the end of each page or as endnotes, and so on). See \'93Adjusting This Template\'94 (below) for information on how to tweak your project to meet different requirements.\
\

\fs36 \cf2 How To Use This Template
\fs24 \cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Edit the \'93Title Page\'94 document so that it contains the title of your essay, your instructor\'92s name and so on.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Compose your essay in text documents inside the \'93Main Content\'94 folder. Whether you use a single document or multiple text files to write your essay is entirely up to you\'97just make sure they are all inside the \'93Main Content\'94 folder.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Indent block quotes or other special passages using styles. For instance, to add a block quote, choose \'93Block Quote\'94 from the Format > Style menu (or from the styles button in the format bar).\
{\listtext	\'95	}This template includes an \'93Endnotes\'94 document which can be used to hold any footnotes you have created in the main body of the text. If you have not created any footnotes, or if you wish to have footnotes added at the end of the page rather than the end of the document, you should either delete this document or deselect its \'93Include in Compile\'94 setting in the Inspector or Compile sheet.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Edit the \'93Works Cited\'94 file so that it contains your own bibliography, being careful to adhere to the Chicago style for the citations. Some notes on the style required for citations are provided in the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivlnk://E14D2E77-2F93-45A5-B464-E2EAF01E542B"}}{\fldrslt Works Cited Format}} document. If you do not require a \'93Works Cited\'94 page, either delete this document or deselect its \'93Include in Compile\'94 setting in the Inspector or Compile sheet.\
