\fs36 \cf2 Compiling
\fs24 \cf0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Go to File > Compile\'85\
{\listtext	\'95	}Ensure the \'93Chicago Essay\'94 format is selected in the list of formats on the left of the Compile panel.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Be sure to fill in information such as author and title in the metadata pane (click on the tag icon in the right-most header bar of Compile).\
{\listtext	\'95	}If you wish footnotes to be exported as endnotes, click on the gear icon in the right-most header bar of Compile and tick both \'93Export inspector footnotes as endnotes\'94 and \'93Export inline footnotes as endnotes\'94. (Be sure to remove the \'93Notes\'94 document if you do this.)\
{\listtext	\'95	}Click \'93Compile\'94.\
